# Vyotiq engineering standards

## Ship real work
- No placeholder UI, stub IPC handlers, or fake workflows in user-facing paths.
- Integrate with existing stores, IPC (`src/shared/types/ipc.ts`), settings persistence, and tests.

## Code quality
- Minimal scope; match existing patterns in the touched area.
- **Search before creating files** — extend `src/main/`, `src/renderer/`, `src/shared/` modules when overlap exists.
- One tool per file under `src/main/tools/`; feature folders under `components/`, not monoliths.

## Always-on desktop agent (memory)
- Cleanup: `useEffect` return handlers, `removeListener`, clear intervals, dispose PTY/LSP/watchers on workspace switch.
- IPC: typed `vyotiq.*` invoke; avoid listener accumulation in renderer (`chatChannel.ts` pattern).
- Main: null `BrowserWindow` refs on `closed`; stop pollers/watchers on quit.

## Consistency
- Tailwind v4 CSS-first tokens in `src/renderer/index.css` — no hardcoded hex in components.
- Shell Mono aesthetic; reuse `vx-*`, `SurfaceShell`, feature CSS (`dock-flyout.css`, etc.).
- Never remove existing features without explicit user request.

## Verify
- Targeted Vitest + `pnpm build` after renderer/CSS changes.
- Authoritative context: `AGENTS.md`, `project.md`.
